innesota/hennepin/", "3/united states/minnesota/hennepin/minneapolis/", "2/united states/minnesota/ramsey/", "3/united states/minnesota/ramsey/saint paul/"], "contributor": ["minnesota historical society; saint paul, mn"], "date": "1949-02-10", "dates": ["1949-02-10"], "description": ["Pge Two Twin City Observer Bex 95 Tnrrtt States Miaaeapete IX Minn atlitM G WUBaaaa Owner and Futtisaer Mlites G WUBaaaa Editor EARL SIMS Advertence PL 2835 ESTYR BRADLEY PEAKE St Paul Representative 854 Ikhart Avenue Dale 8825 MART KYLE Mmaeapobs Representative 3437 4th Ave So __ LOcust 7850 ALLIE B GLENN CirculationAdvertising Entered as ond class matter March 8 1945 at the post office at Minneapolis 1 Minnesota under Act of March 3 1879 flcrrv bTMmb EDITORIAL It is just as dSicult for city residents to look at things from the farmers viewpoint as it is for the farmer to understand the problems of those who live in the cities But it isnt too dfhcult for us to understand the position the farmer is in a he suddenly discovers that the prices he re ceives for his products are suffering harp reductionsreduc tions it is needless to say much faster and much greater than those which the consumer yet has to pay The farmer is in the ame position that a man who works for a wage or salary uld be in if he were to be informed when he starts to work netx Monday that his wage or"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-07-10T20:54:17.462Z", "group": ["ndnp/mnhi", "minnesota-historical-society-saint-paul-mn-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn83016844/1949-02-10/ed-1/?sp=2", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_iago_ver01:data:sn83016844:00542865349:1949021001:1081/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=413&w=303", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:mnhi:batch_mnhi_iago_ver01:data:sn83016844:00542865349:1949021001:1081/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=826&w=606", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word